result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin C. Chmiel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Victim/Use or Attempt Force [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.45(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Justin C. Chmiel in court with Attorney Jonathan A. Lavoy.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Becky Van Dam appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Counts #2 & 3 are dismissed and read-in.  Victim makes statements.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Lavoy makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  WITHHELD SENTENCE

TERM OF PROBATION:  30 MONTHS    (8 Days credit, if revoked)    **CONCURRENT**   

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribedsign releases 
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No violent or abusive contact with: victim
____Domestic Violence Counseling through a State Certified Batterers Intervention Program such as  	Alliance Counseling or Family Services of Waukesha;
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done
____50 Hours of Community Service- to be completed within 1st year of probation

COSTS:  $268.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted and remainder to be returned to poster)
